<subSubSection pageId="53" pageNumber="52" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="53.[813,1456,657,866]" pageId="53" pageNumber="52">
Species resembling 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cavaco &amp; Keraudren" authorityYear="1956" box="[1004,1121,657,680]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Xylopia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="53" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capuronii">
<emphasis box="[1004,1121,657,680]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="52">X. capuronii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Johnson &amp; Murray, 2020" authorityName="D. M. Johnson &amp; N. A. Murray" authorityYear="2020" box="[1173,1293,657,681]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Xylopia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="53" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lokobensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1173,1293,657,681]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="52">X. lokobensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1306,1387,657,680]" pageId="53" pageNumber="52" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, in the subcoriaceous leaves, sepals exceeding 
<quantity box="[1188,1247,683,707]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="53" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
in length, and broad acute outer petals, but differing from the former in the recurved rather than strongly revolute leaf margins and the sparse yellow-brown rather than dense dull red indument of the twigs and leaves, from the latter in the longer pubescence of the twigs and the recurved rather than flat leaf margins, and from both species in the more pronounced keel on the abaxial surface of the outer petals.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
